                <h2>How to Choose the Right Air Purifier</h2>
                <p>Selecting an air purifier isn't just about grabbing the most expensive model; it's about matching the machine's capabilities to your specific needs and room size. The two most critical numbers to look at are the CADR (Clean Air Delivery Rate) and the stated coverage area.</p>
                <p>As a rule of thumb, you want a purifier that can change the air in your room at least 4 times per hour (ACH - Air Changes per Hour) on its highest setting. If you place a unit rated for 150 sq. ft. into a 400 sq. ft. living room, it won't be able to cycle the air fast enough to meaningfully improve the overall air quality.</p>

                <h2>Understanding Filter Types: HEPA vs. Carbon</h2>
                <p>Air purifiers typically use a combination of mechanical filters to clean the air. Understanding what each layer does helps you determine which machine is best for your specific problems:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>True HEPA Filters:</strong> The gold standard for particulate filtration. They are certified to capture at least 99.97% of particles as small as 0.3 microns. This is essential for removing dust, pollen, pet dander, mold spores, and smoke particles.</li>
                    <li><strong>Activated Carbon Filters:</strong> HEPA filters cannot capture gases, VOCs (Volatile Organic Compounds), or odors. Activated carbon chemically binds these molecules. For severe odor or smoke issues, look for units with actual carbon pellets rather than thin carbon-impregnated sheets.</li>
                    <li><strong>Pre-filters:</strong> Usually washable mesh that captures large hair and dust before it hits the expensive HEPA filter, significantly extending its lifespan.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>What About UV Lights and Ionizers?</h2>
                <p>Many air purifiers include secondary technologies like UV-C light or ionizers. UV light is theoretically used to kill viruses and bacteria, but in a typical home purifier, the air moves too fast past the bulb for it to be highly effective. Ionizers release negative ions to clump particles together so they fall to the floor or are easily caught by the filter. However, ionizers can produce ozone as a byproduct, which is a lung irritant. If you buy a unit with an ionizer (like the Coway Mighty or Winix 5500-2), we generally recommend keeping that specific feature turned off.</p>
            </div>
        </main>

        
    </div>
  <script is:inline>
// Search/Filter Functionality
        const searchInput = document.getElementById('searchInput');
        const contentSections = document.querySelectorAll('.content-section');
        const searchableItems = document.querySelectorAll('.searchable-item');
        const noResultsMessage = document.getElementById('noResults');

        searchInput.addEventListener('input', function(e) {
            const searchTerm = e.target.value.toLowerCase().trim();
            let totalVisibleItems = 0;

            if (searchTerm === '') {
                // Reset everything if search is empty
                searchableItems.forEach(item => item.classList.remove('hidden'));
                contentSections.forEach(section => section.classList.remove('hidden'));
                noResultsMessage.style.display = 'none';
                return;
            }

            // Filter items within sections
            contentSections.forEach(section => {
                let sectionHasVisibleItems = false;
                const sectionItems = section.querySelectorAll('.searchable-item');

                // Check if the section tags themselves match the search
                const sectionTags = section.getAttribute('data-tags') || '';
                const sectionMatches = sectionTags.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm) ||
                                     section.querySelector('h2').textContent.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm);

                sectionItems.forEach(item => {
                    const searchableText = (item.getAttribute('data-search') || '') + ' ' +
                                         (item.textContent || '').toLowerCase();

                    if (sectionMatches || searchableText.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm)) {
                        item.classList.remove('hidden');
                        sectionHasVisibleItems = true;
                        totalVisibleItems++;
                    } else {
                        item.classList.add('hidden');
                    }
                });

                // Hide the whole section if it has no matching items
                if (sectionHasVisibleItems || sectionMatches) {
                    section.classList.remove('hidden');
                    // If section matches but items don't, show all items in that section
                    if (sectionMatches && !sectionHasVisibleItems) {
                        sectionItems.forEach(item => {
                            item.classList.remove('hidden');
                            totalVisibleItems++;
                        });
                    }
                } else {
                    section.classList.add('hidden');
                }
            });

            // Show 'No Results' message if necessary
            if (totalVisibleItems === 0) {
                noResultsMessage.style.display = 'block';
            } else {
                noResultsMessage.style.display = 'none';
            }
        });
  </script>
</SiteLayout>
